                            <comment id="12679142" author="chrisdutz" created="Thu, 5 Mar 2009 10:29:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;All that has to be done to resonve this issue, is to change the order of two code fragments in the method writeObjectInternal&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here the blocks:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;for (Iterator itr = inf.getElements(); itr.hasNext()&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; {&lt;br/&gt;
    ...&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if (inf.isExtension()) {&lt;br/&gt;
    ...&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;simply have to be swapped to output the extended type first.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12679332" author="bmargulies" created="Thu, 5 Mar 2009 20:15:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Could you post your fix as a patch, please? (diff -u)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12679431" author="bmargulies" created="Thu, 5 Mar 2009 23:57:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Are you sure we want to run the extension code between the attributes and the elements? I guess attribute order doesn&apos;t matter.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12679432" author="bmargulies" created="Thu, 5 Mar 2009 23:58:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fix applied to trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12679562" author="chrisdutz" created="Fri, 6 Mar 2009 11:27:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I haven&apos;t had a real deep look into how data is processed. The main problem was that the order was simply not schema valid.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I guss to make it really fool-proof it would be necessary to do a two-phase processing ... &lt;br/&gt;
1. Process attributes of current- and parent-types&lt;br/&gt;
2. Process the elements of the parents and then of the current type&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tanks for patching &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
When will with be available as compiled maven-artifact?&lt;br/&gt;
I am curently using a local artifact of version 2.1.4 with the applied patch, as I sort of had problems building a 2.1.4.1 version ...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12679574" author="bmargulies" created="Fri, 6 Mar 2009 12:16:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you are in a hurry, and will work with trunk, I&apos;ll make a snapshot. If you need 2.1.x, someone will have to do a merge down first.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
